#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/supernovae.rst:3
msgid "Supernovae"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/supernovae.rst:5
msgid "|Supernovae Window|"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/supernovae.rst:7
msgid ""
"The ``Supernovae`` page allows you to decide if the supernovae are displayed "
"or not by checking the ``Show supernovae`` checkbox. By default, supernovae "
"are drawn as small light orange “+” mark.  As for satellites, the color of "
"supernovae can be easily customized using the ``Colors`` page."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/supernovae.rst:9
msgid ""
"You can set the magnitude limit for showing a supernova as well as magnitude "
"limit for supernova alerts using the spin boxes control. The limiting "
"magnitude is the faintest apparent magnitude of an skyobject that is visible "
"with the naked-eye or a telescope."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../user_manual/supernovae.rst:11
msgid ""
"The list of recent supernovae can be updated via the ``Data`` → ``Updates`` "
"→ ``Update Recent Supernovae data`` menu item."
msgstr ""

